The virus lives in tiny droplets in the lungs of people w/ COVID-19, even when they don’t show symptoms. We can breathe the same air as anyone within abt. 6 ft. of us. Staying farther apart from people during this time reduces the chance of breathing in the virus. #StayHomeTexas

El virus vive en gotas en los pulmones de personas con COVID-19, y a veces no tienen síntomas. Puedes respirar el mismo aire que cualquiera a 6 pies de ti. Mantente más alejado de las personas durante este tiempo para reducir la posibilidad de respirar el virus. #StayHomeTexas

Coughing & sneezing can send tiny infected droplets into the air which can be inhaled by anyone within 6 feet of us. Always cough or sneeze into a tissue or your elbow and immediately wash your hands to lessen the risk of spreading the virus. Be smart. Stay well! #StayHomeTexas

Toser y estornudar puede llevar gotas infectadas al aire, que pueden ser inhaladas por personas que estén a 6 pies de ti. Siempre tosa o estornude en pañuelos desechables o en el codo y lávese las manos para disminuir la propagación del virus. ¡Mantente sano! #StayHomeTexas

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Los síntomas comunes de #COVID19 son fiebre, tos seca y dificultad para respirar.Si tiene síntomas leves, llame a su médico y quedate en casa.Si desarrolla síntomas graves, como dificultad para respirar o presión en el pecho, busque atención médica de inmediato. #StayHome

Before social distancing, each person with #COVID19 spread the virus to 2.5 more people. At that pace, most would get it, and many more people would die. But we can slow the spread. That’s why we all #StayHome. #ApartTogether we slow coronavirus.

Antes del distanciamiento social, cada persona con #COVID19 transmitió el virus a 2.5 personas. A ese ritmo, muchas personas se contagiarían, y muchas personas morirían. Pero podemos retrasar la propagación. Por eso todos quedémonos en casa y paremos el Coronavirus.#ApartTogether

post_text:
Practice Social Distancing

To avoid the spread of COVID-19 in our community, practice social distancing:
• Avoid going out in public
• When in public, keep six feet of distance between you and others
• Follow guidance provided by local and state officials.
Get more information at https://texas.gov/covid19
#covid19 #texasstrong #stayhome

Practica el Distanciamiento Social

Para prevenir la propagación de COVID-19 en nuestra comunidad, practique el distanciamiento social:
• Evite salir en público
• Cuando esté en público, mantenga una distancia de seis pies entre usted y los demás.
• Seguir las recomendaciones de los funcionarios locales y estatales.
Obtenga más información en https://texas.gov/covid19
# covid19 #texasfuerte #quedateencasa

3. Aprenda Mas sobre el desempeño de su hijo, incluyendo como se contestaron las preguntas y como puede proporcionar apoyo adicional en el hogar.

1. Starting June 13th, visit TexasAssessment.com
2. Log in with your child’s STAAR Access Code or use the Access Code Look-Up Feature at TexasAssessment.com.
3. Learn more about your child’s performance, including how questions were answered, and how you can provide additional support at home.

To all our Families and Staff:
Excellence in Leadership Academy reminds you that our value of the month is Gratitude. May we continue to actively live out our I Wills...every day. As we educate our children and future generations, we emphasize that integrity, hard work and character can catapult them into leadership positions where they will be able to positively impact our society. May you enjoy this Thanksgiving with family and friends!

Para todas nuestras Familias y Personal:
Excellence in Leadership Academy les recuerda que nuestro valor del mes es Gratitud. Les aliento a que sigamos activamente viviendo nuestros Yo Decidos...cada dia. Al educar a nuestros ninos y las generaciones futuras, enfatizamos que la integridad, trabajo, y caracter pueden catapultarlos hacia posiciones de liderazgo donde puedan hacer un impacto positivo para nuestra sociedad. Nuestro deseo es que disfruten de este Dia de Dar Gracias con familia y amistades!

post_text:
See You at the Pole (SYATP) is an annual gathering of thousands of Christian students at a flagpole in front of their local school for prayer, scripture-reading and worship, during the early morning before school starts. The American SYATP events occur on the 28 of September at 7:00 A.M. while gathering around a school flag pole.The events began in 1990 in the United States, where public schools cannot sponsor prayers. It has grown by word of mouth, announcements at youth rallies and churches, and the Internet. It is now an international event. Come join us for:
See You at the Pole Wednesday, September 28, 2016 at 7:00 am.

As we prepare for the beginning of the 2015-2016 school year, we will be posting information to help you and your child(ren) transition from summer to the beginning of classes. Attached is the list of school supplies and our 2015-16 school calendar. Our Summer office hours are from Monday - Thursday from 8:00 am - 5:30 pm. Our office number is: (956) 424-9504. We will be serving students from PK-4 to 6th grade. Continue to encourage your child to READ, READ, READ!
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Como preparacion para el principio del ano escolar 2015-2016, les estaremos proporcionando informacion para ayudarles con la transicion del verano al principio de clases. Adjunto se encuentran la lista de utiles escolares y el calendario escolar para el 2015-2016. Nuestro horario de oficina durante el verano es de Lunes a Jueves de 8:00 am- 5:30 pm. Nuestro numero telefonico es: (956) 424-9504. Estaremos proveyendo servicios a estudiantes de PK-4 a 6to grado. Continue animando a su hijo/a a LEER, LEER, LEER!

We will be hosting a Parent Conference on April 16, Thursday, at 6:30 pm at the ELA Auditorium. Dr. J. G. Reyes will be our Presenter. The topic for this Parent Conference is "Prepare your Child for the Real World". Child care will be provided. Students who bring their Parents will receive $50 Eagle Bucks. Come and take advantage of this opportunity to gain additional information on how you, as a Parent, can make a significant impact now for your child's future.

Estaremos proveendo una Conferencia para Padres el 16 de Abril, Jueves, a las 6:30 pm en el Auditorio de ELA. El Dr. J. G. Reyes sera nuestro Orador. El tema de esta Conferencia para Padres es
"Prepare a su Hijo para el Mundo Real". Se proveera Guarderia para los ninos. Los estudiantes que traigan a sus Padres recibiran $50 Eagle Bucks. Venga y aproveche esta oportunidad para obtener mas informacion acerca de como Ud., como Padre, puede hacer un impacto significativo ahora para el future de su nino/a.

post_text:
Excellence in Leadership Academy will be participating in the Texas Citrus Fiesta Parade this Saturday, at 3:00 pm. on Conway St. in Mission, Texas. We will be float #58. We will also have a booth:
Nachos, Frito Pie, Sodas, Water, Pickles, etc. on Conway & 8th St. (across from HEB). We continue accepting donations. You may drop them off at the school. If you are interested in helping out at the booth, please contact our office. We appreciate all your support. We'll see you on Saturday!

Excellence in Leadership Academy estara participando en el desfile Texas Citrus Fiesta este sabado a las 3:00 pm por la calle Conway en Mission, Texas. Nuestro carro alegorico sera el #58. Tambien, tendremos un puesto: Nacho, Frito Pie, sodas, aguas, pepinos, etc. en Conway & 8th St. (en frente del HEB). Continuamos aceptando donaciones. Puede entregarlas en la escuela. Si esta interesado en ayudar en el puesto, por favor de comunicarse con nosotros en la oficina. Agradecemos todo su apoyo. Nos vemos el Sabado!

We will be sharing information about our School's Report Card, the Family Handbook, and the Title I Program. Our Parents will also be electing new PTO Officers for this school year. Saturday, May 24, 2014
9:00 - 11:30

Our students will set up their "Business" in our front parking lot. Ms. Cyda Alfaro, Business Manager, provided the students with tips on how to successfully begin their own business. This is part of our Financial Literacy Curriculum. Please come by (bring guests) and support our students as they initiate their "business endeavors".

Por favor, venga (invite a otros) y apoye los esfuerzos de nuestros estudiantes al iniciar sus "negocios".

post_text: Lizzie Sider, a 15 year old Country Music rising artist, visited Excellence in Leadership Academy as part of her tour of schools across the country campaigning against bullying. It was an honor to have her at our school. Our students, staff and parents were not only entertained, but greatly moved by her message against bullying, "Nobody has the power to ruin your day!". Thank you, Lizzie, for visiting our school and we know we will be hearing more about you in the near future!

As we begin a new School Year, 2013-14, we invite you to come by and visit our campus and meet our staff. During the summer, we have made renovations to our facility to accommodate the growing number of our student population. This year we will be serving students from PK to 4th Grade. We are an open-enrollment, tuition-free, public charter school with a focus on leadership, principles & values, and dual language program. Come and find out more about our school at our Family Fun & Orientation Night August 16th from 6:00 - 9:00 pm. We will have children's games and a car show. On-site tours and an opportunity to meet the staff will be provided.
915 W. Expressway 83 Mission, Texas
(956) 424-9504

ANNOUNCEMENT:
Excellence in Leadership Academy is holding its 1st King and Queen Gala on Thursday, May 23rd, at 6:30 pm at the ELA Auditorium. Tickets are on sale at the ELA office for $15.00. A formal dinner will be provided. Formal Attire is required. Come and be a part of this exciting historical event.

post_text: A big THANK YOU to all who donated for our ART AUCTION: Dr. Jose G. Reyes, Robert Rodriguez, Homero Cantu, Juan Lopez, Eva Castilleja, Israel L. Lopez, Lupita Gonzalez, Marichu Urcullu, Juan J. Morales, Marco A. Lopez, Alma Munoz, and all our STUDENTS.

post_text: Our Talent Show was a great success. Singing "Panis Angelicus", Jannette Rodriguez took the trophy for the Adult Category. With a song and dance, our own Pre-K student Emily Hernandez won the trophy for the Children's Category. Congratulations to Jannette and Emily and all our Participants!

post_text: On February 1st, we are celebrating our first 100 school days with a school parade. Our theme is "We are 100 school days smarter!" Students are encouraged to dress with an outfit containing 100 items: buttons, pins, bows, beads, patches, etc. This is a joint project between parent(s) and student. Let's be creative and have fun. / El 1 de Febrero estaremos celebrando nuestros primeros 100 dias escolares con un desfile escolar. Nuestro tema es: "Somos 100 dias escolares mas inteligentes!" Animamos a los estudiantes a usar un traje que contenga 100 objetos: botones, seguros, broches, cuentas, parches, etc. Este es un proyecto conjunto entre padre(s) y estudiante. Seamos creativos y disfrutemos!

PK/Kinder School Supplies

1 pack of sharpened #2 pencils (12 count)/1 paquete de lápices con punta #2
2 large pink erasers/2 borradores rosas
1 ruler (12 inch)/1 regla (12 pulgadas)
1 pair Fiskar scissors/ 1 tijeras Fiskar
2 composition notebooks/2 cuadernos de composición de escritura
1 8 oz hand sanitizer / 1 8 oz desinfectante para manos
1 box Ziploc sandwich bags/1 caja de bolsas Ziploc tamaño sandwich
1 box of Ziploc gallon size/1 caja de bolsas Ziploc (galón)
1 box of tissue/1 caja de pañuelos desechables (Kleenex)
2 glue sticks/2 pegamentos de barra
1 box of crayons (24 count)/1 caja de crayolas
1 package of baby wipes/1 paquete de toallitas húmedas
1 box of washable markers/1 caja de plumones
1 bottle Elmer’s glue/1 bote de pegamento
5 folders with brads/5 folders con puntillas
1 box of water colors (8ct)/1 caja pinturitas de agua
1 highlighter /1 marcatextos
1 change of clothes with name/1 cambio de ropa con su nombre

post_text:
Excellence in Leadership Academy needs your Box Tops for Education coupons. As you purchase school supplies, ziploc baggies, hefty disposable plates, cups and many other items that have the Box Tops for Education, clip those out and forward them to our school. Each box top coupon is worth 10 cents but during the "Back to School" sales, they may be worth up to 4 times the value ( 40 cents). Let's raise funds for our school. Clip those Box Tops and bringing them in. Thank you!

Excellence in Leadership Academy necesita sus cupones de Box Tops for Education. Al comprar los utiles escolares, bolsitas ziploc, deshechables de Hefty, y muchos otros articulos que traen el Box Tops for Education, cortelos y hagalos llegar a nuestra escuela. Cada cupon tiene el valor de .10 pero durante las ventas de "Regreso a la Escuela" pueden valer hasta .40 centavos. Ayudenos a recaudar fondos para nuestra escuela. Corte los Box Tops y entreguelos a Excellence in Leadership Academy. Gracias!
